<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figures 35 - 38. Cerci and subgenital plate of male of Morgenia rubricornis (35 lateral, 36 ventral) and M. hamuligera (37 lateral, 38 ventral)." , "Figures 19 - 22. Stridulatory file of the left tegmen in the male of Morgenia rubricornis (19), M. hamuligera (20), M. plurimaculata sp. n. (21) and M. lehmannorum sp. n. (22)." , "Figures 9 - 14. Stridulatory area of left tegmen and mirror of right tegmen of the male of Morgenia hamuligera (9), M. rubricornis (10), M. spathulifera (11), M. lehmannorum sp. n. (12); habitus of M. hamuligera after Brunner von Wattenwyl (1878) (13) and of M. rubricornis after Sjoestedt (1913) (14). Arrow shows the particular net of small cells in the costal area of tegmina of M. spathulifera, present also in M. lehmannorum sp. n." , "Figures 27 - 34. Mid tibia showing the inner spur in the male of Morgenia hamuligera (27), M. rubricornis (28), M. plurimaculata sp. n. (29), M. lehmannorum sp. n. (30), M. angustipinnata sp. n. (31), M. spathulifera (32), M. melica (33) and M. modulata (34)." , "Figures 1 - 4. Habitus of the male of Morgenia hamuligera (1), M. rubricornis (2), M. plurimaculata sp. n. (3) and M. lehmannorum sp. n. (4) (left side for the first three species, right side for the fourth species)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/220914" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/220915" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/220912" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/220908" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/220910" .

